  "instructions_to_main_agent": [
    "This is a React Native Expo app. DO NOT USE Web APIs like HTML/CSS/Tailwind classnames directly unless using NativeWind.",
    "Use StyleSheet or a library like NativeWind for styling. Stick to the provided exact hex colors. Never use generic blue/red/teal colors.",
    "For the bottom navigation and top headers, apply `expo-blur` (BlurView) for a 'Crystal Glass' effect over scrolling content.",
    "All interactive elements MUST include `testID` attribute (e.g., `testID=\"login-button\"`) as this is React Native, mapping to the 'data-testid' testing requirement.",
    "Ensure the gold color (#D4A437) is used sparingly as an accent to indicate status, active states, and premium features.",
    "Typography requires `@expo-google-fonts/cormorant-garamond` for Headings and `@expo-google-fonts/outfit` for Body. Ensure fonts are loaded in the root layout before rendering.",
    "Keep standard RN UI elements styled: No default ugly inputs. Customize text inputs with bottom borders (OTP) or padded rounded backgrounds (chat inputs) matching `surface_level_2`.",
    "Ensure all lists use `FlatList` with sensible `contentContainerStyle` paddings so items don't hit the screen edges."
  ]
}